General Shortcuts
Ctrl + C: Copy

Ctrl + X: Cut

Ctrl + V: Paste

Ctrl + Z: Undo

Ctrl + Y: Redo

Ctrl + A: Select all

Alt + Tab: Switch between open apps

Alt + F4: Close the active window

Windows + D: Show or hide the desktop

Windows + L: Lock your PC

Windows Key Shortcuts
Windows + E: Open File Explorer

Windows + I: Open Settings

Windows + S: Open Search

Windows + R: Open the Run dialog box

Windows + X: Open the Quick Link menu

Windows + Tab: Open Task View

Windows + A: Open Quick Settings

Windows + N: Open Notification Center and Calendar

Windows + W: Open Widgets

Windows + K: Open Cast from Quick Settings

Windows + H: Launch voice typing

Windows + G: Open Xbox Game Bar

Windows + P: Open Project menu (for switching display modes)

Windows + M: Minimize all open windows

Windows + Shift + M: Restore minimized windows on the desktop

Windows + V: Open Clipboard history (if enabled)

Windows + . (period): Open emoji panel

File Explorer Shortcuts
Ctrl + N: Open a new window

Ctrl + W: Close the current window

Ctrl + Shift + N: Create a new folder

Alt + D: Select the address bar

Ctrl + Shift + E: Display all folders above the selected folder

Ctrl + F: Search for a file or folder

F2: Rename the selected item

F11: Maximize or minimize the active window

Taskbar Shortcuts
Windows + T: Cycle through apps on the taskbar

Windows + Number (0-9): Open the app pinned to the taskbar in the position indicated by the number

Windows + Alt + Number (0-9): Open the Jump List for the app pinned to the taskbar in the position indicated by the number

Windows + Ctrl + Number (0-9): Switch to the last active window of the app pinned to the taskbar in the position indicated by the number

Virtual Desktop Shortcuts
Windows + Ctrl + D: Add a virtual desktop

Windows + Ctrl + Right Arrow: Switch to the virtual desktop on the right

Windows + Ctrl + Left Arrow: Switch to the virtual desktop on the left

Windows + Ctrl + F4: Close the current virtual desktop
